                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 space-y-20">
        <article id="overview" class="bg-white rounded-3xl shadow-xl p-8 md:p-12 border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-2xl transition-shadow duration-300">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-8">
                <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-100 to-indigo-100 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                    <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-800" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4"></path>
                    </svg>
                </div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-800 to-blue-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">Understanding Property Law & Conveyancing in South Africa</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
                Property law in South Africa governs the rights individuals and entities hold over various objects, particularly land and buildings. It is a complex field that ensures secure ownership and regulates property transactions. <strong>Conveyancing</strong> is the specialized legal process of transferring legal ownership of immovable property from one party to another, accurately registering these changes with the Deeds Office. Our expert team ensures that every step, from sale agreements to final registration, is handled with precision and compliance with South African law.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-800 to-blue-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
                Common Types of Property Ownership in South Africa
            </h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-blue-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all group">
                    <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-800 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mr-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
                            <i class="fas fa-home text-white w-6 h-6"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Freehold Ownership</h3>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">You own both the land and the dwelling on it, granting you full control over the property and its use, subject to municipal regulations.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-purple-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-indigo-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all group">
                    <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-indigo-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mr-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
                            <i class="fas fa-building text-white w-6 h-6"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Sectional Title Ownership</h3>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">You own a specific unit (e.g., apartment, townhouse) within a complex, and a share in the common property. Governed by a Body Corporate.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-pink-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-purple-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all group">
                    <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-purple-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mr-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
                            <i class="fas fa-file-contract text-white w-6 h-6"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Leasehold Ownership</h3>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">Grants the right to use a property for a specified period, typically a long-term lease, without owning the underlying land outright.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="bg-white rounded-3xl shadow-xl overflow-hidden">
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-800 to-blue-600 p-10">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white text-center">The Property Conveyancing Process</h2>
                <p class="text-white/90 text-center mt-4 text-lg">A step-by-step guide to secure property transfer</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-8 md:p-12">
                <div class="space-y-8">
                    <div class="flex items-start group">
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-800 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform shadow-lg">
                            <i class="fas fa-handshake"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-6 flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Offer to Purchase (OTP)</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">The process begins with a legally binding Offer to Purchase, outlining the sale terms and conditions agreed upon by buyer and seller.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flex items-start group">
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-700 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform shadow-lg">
                            <i class="fas fa-user-tie"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-6 flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Appointment of Conveyancer</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">The seller typically appoints a qualified conveyancer to manage the legal transfer process and ensure compliance with all regulations.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flex items-start group">
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform shadow-lg">
                            <i class="fas fa-money-check-alt"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-6 flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Bond Approval & Guarantees</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">If financing is required, the buyer secures a home loan. The bank then appoints a bond attorney to register the bond simultaneously with the property transfer at the Deeds Office.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flex items-start group">
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform shadow-lg">
                            <i class="fas fa-certificate"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-6 flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Obtaining Clearance Certificates</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">The seller must obtain various municipal (rates), levy (for sectional titles), electrical, gas, plumbing, and beetle (if applicable) compliance certificates before transfer can proceed.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flex items-start group">
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-400 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform shadow-lg">
                            <i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-6 flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Payments & Document Signing</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">The buyer pays transfer duty to SARS and conveyancing fees. Both parties sign crucial transfer documents, including the Power of Attorney to Pass Transfer, under the guidance of the conveyancer.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flex items-start group">
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-300 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform shadow-lg">
                            <i class="fas fa-landmark"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-6 flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Lodgement at Deeds Office</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">All prepared and signed documents, including the title deed and bond documents, are lodged at the relevant Deeds Office for examination and approval, a critical step in the transfer.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flex items-start group">
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-200 text-blue-800 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform shadow-lg">
                            <i class="fas fa-key"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-6 flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Registration & Handover</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">Once approved by the Deeds Office, the property is officially registered in the buyer's name. The buyer takes legal ownership, and the keys are typically handed over on this date.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-800 to-blue-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
                Essential Documents for Property Transfer
            </h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-blue-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
                        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-blue-800 mr-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v9a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V8m-2 0V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H9a2 2 0 00-2 2v3m7 0h-3l2-2m0 0l2 2"></path>
                        </svg>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">For the Buyer</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-file-contract text-blue-800 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Signed Offer to Purchase</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">The primary agreement outlining the terms of sale, signed by both buyer and seller.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-id-card text-blue-800 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">FICA Documents (ID & Proof of Address)</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Mandatory identification and verification documents as per the Financial Intelligence Centre Act.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-receipt text-blue-800 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Transfer Duty Receipt</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Proof of tax payment to SARS on the property transfer, issued once paid.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-piggy-bank text-blue-800 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Bond Approval (if applicable)</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Confirmation of home loan approval from a financial institution, along with required bank documents.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-purple-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-indigo-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
                        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-indigo-700 mr-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"></path>
                        </svg>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">For the Seller</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-scroll text-indigo-700 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Original Title Deed</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">The current proof of ownership of the property, required by the Deeds Office.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-city text-indigo-700 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Rates Clearance Certificate</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Confirms all municipal rates and taxes are paid up to date, issued by the local municipality.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-tools text-indigo-700 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Compliance Certificates</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Includes mandatory electrical, gas, and plumbing certificates. A beetle certificate may be required if the property is in a high-risk area or specified in the OTP.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-hand-point-right text-indigo-700 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Power of Attorney to Pass Transfer</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">A legal document signed by the seller, authorising the conveyancer to act on their behalf to transfer the property.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-800 to-blue-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
                Costs Associated with Property Transfer
            </h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-blue-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
                        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-blue-800 mr-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 9V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2m2 4h10a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H9a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm7-5a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"></path>
                        </svg>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Buyer's Costs</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-percentage text-blue-800 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Transfer Duty</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">A government tax payable to SARS on the property's purchase price. Properties below R1.1 million are currently exempt (as of 1 March 2024).</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-calculator text-blue-800 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Conveyancing Fees</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Legal fees charged by the conveyancer for handling the transfer, typically calculated based on a recommended tariff from the Legal Practice Council (LPC).</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-university text-blue-800 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Bond Registration Costs</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Fees for registering the mortgage bond at the Deeds Office, paid to the bond attorney (if applicable).</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-purple-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-indigo-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
                        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-indigo-700 mr-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m-6 9l2 2 4-4"></path>
                        </svg>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Seller's Costs</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-file-invoice-dollar text-indigo-700 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Compliance Certificates</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Costs for obtaining necessary electrical, gas, and plumbing certificates, and potentially a beetle certificate.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-ban text-indigo-700 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Bond Cancellation Costs</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Fees charged by the bond cancellation attorney to cancel an existing mortgage bond on the property.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-xl p-4 flex items-start">
                            <i class="fas fa-hand-holding-usd text-indigo-700 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0"></i>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Estate Agent Commission</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">If an estate agent facilitated the sale, their commission (usually a percentage of the sale price) is typically paid by the seller.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-800 to-blue-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
                Key South African Property Legislation
            </h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-blue-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all group">
                    <div class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-800 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mr-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"></path>
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">The Constitution of SA, 1996</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">Section 25 (Property Clause) protects property rights and regulates deprivation/expropriation.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-purple-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-indigo-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all group">
                    <div class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-indigo-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mr-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
                            <i class="fas fa-file-invoice text-white w-6 h-6"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Deeds Registries Act 47 of 1937</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">Governs the registration of deeds and property rights in South Africa, ensuring security of title.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-pink-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-purple-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all group">
                    <div class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-purple-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mr-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
                            <i class="fas fa-gavel text-white w-6 h-6"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Alienation of Land Act 68 of 1981</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">Prescribes formalities for contracts of sale of land to ensure their validity and enforceability.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-red-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-pink-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all group">
                    <div class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mr-4 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
                            <i class="fas fa-building text-white w-6 h-6"></i>
                        </div>
