                        <p>A conveyancer is a qualified attorney who specializes in property law and is responsible for ensuring the lawful and efficient transfer of ownership of immovable property from one person or entity to another. They handle all legal aspects, including drafting and preparing documents, liaising with the Deeds Office and other parties (like banks and municipalities), and managing all finances related to the transfer.</p>
